  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The <span>Hôtel Nendaz 4 Vallées &amp; Spa is available on a half board basis. </span></p>
<p>Fuel up for the day at the varied breakfast buffet which includes various sweet and savoury options.</p>
<p>Each evening you can enjoy a three course evening meal with two choices, in the modern Le Clos des Cimes restaurant. You can also dine in the cosy Le Carnotzet l'Aigle, serving Swiss specialities including fondue and raclette. Additional charges may apply for Carnotzet l'Aigle. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>The Hôtel Nendaz 4 Vallées &amp; Spa offers luxurious and comfortable accommodation in the <a data-udi="umb://document/88af8226aa3a4c319246d3aea3a37b24" href="/{localLink:umb://document/88af8226aa3a4c319246d3aea3a37b24}" title="Four Vallées" data-anchor="#">Four Vallées</a>. You'll have great access to the slopes and resort centre with a range of shops, bars and restaurants, all of which is just a short walk away. With an extensive wellness area, cosy bedrooms and delicious food, this hotel ticks all the boxes for a Swiss getaway.</span></p>
<h2>Cosy accommodation</h2>
<p>Each bedroom at the <span>Hôtel Nendaz 4 Vallées &amp; Spa is furnished in a traditional yet modern Valasian style with warm wood and cosy furnishings, plus many of the rooms have a bath, so you can relax after a day of exploring Nendaz. Throughout the hotel the contemporary style of the Valais region continues with natural wood and slate. When you return from a day of adventures, sit back and relax with an aperitif in the bar area or take some time to rejuvenate in the extensive wellness area.</span></p>
<h2><span>Spa &amp; wellness</span></h2>
<p><span>After a day of skiing the sunny slopes, the extensive Spa des Bisses wellness area awaits you. Featuring an indoor pool, various </span>saunas, a dew steam bath, an ice cave, Kneipp and relaxation room with mountain views- you have everything needed to thoroughly relax and unwind. The hotel also has an outdoor pool with jacuzzi jets, and views of the surrounding mountain peaks. Soothe your aches and book in for a massage or treatment, available to book locally for a local fee. For those looking to stay active, there is also a fitness room with a range of equipment.</p>
<h2>Food &amp; drink</h2>
<p>Each morning you can fuel up for a day on the slopes at the varied breakfast buffet which includes a variety of sweet and savoury options. When you return from a day of exploring the Four Vallees, you can enjoy a three course evening meal with a menu inspired by the land and sea. If you want to treat yourself to a authentic Swiss meal, Le Carnotzet l'Aigle serves Swiss specialities including raclette, fondue and Valasian dishes - open for lunch and dinner daily.  At the end of the day, catch up with friends and family at the welcoming Piano Bar for a tipple or two. </p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
